# Use Bun Instead of Other Package Managers

Use **bun** instead of other package managers for all JavaScript/TypeScript package management and script running in this project.

## Guidelines

- **Install dependencies**: Use `bun install` (not npm, pnpm, yarn, etc.).
- **Run scripts**: Use `bun run <script>` or `bun <script>` (not npm run, pnpm run, yarn run, etc.).
- **Run a package binary**: Use `bunx <pkg>` (not npx, pnpx, yarn dlx, etc.).
- **Add a dependency**: Use `bun add <pkg>` or `bun add -d <pkg>` (not npm install, pnpm add, yarn add, etc.).

## Scope

- Applies in **frontend/** and any Node/JS/TS work in this repo.
- Python (backend) uses `pip` and `venv`; this rule does not apply there.

## Examples

| Avoid | Use |
|-------|-----|
| `npm install` | `bun install` |
| `pnpm install` | `bun install` |
| `yarn` / `yarn install` | `bun install` |
| `npm run dev` | `bun run dev` or `bun dev` |
| `npx prettier --write .` | `bunx prettier --write .` |
| `pnpm add -D vitest` | `bun add -d vitest` |
| `yarn add lodash` | `bun add lodash` |
